		-----------------------------
		 Useful Terminal I/O Library
		-----------------------------

1. Overview

utio is an alternative (to curses) implementation for terminfo-described
terminal access.

2. Compilation

You will need the uSTL library 2.3 or later to compile utio.
uSTL can be downloaded from https://github.com/msharov/ustl
./configure --help will list available configuration options.

% ./configure && make && make install

Running utio applications requires the terminfo database that
is usually distributed as part of the ncurses package and is
installed in /usr/share/terminfo.

3. Usage

See docs/index.html for API description.

4. Bug reporting

Use the bug trackers at https://github.com/msharov/utio/issues
